abstract: Gymnast Kyla Ross, who won gold medal as youngest member of United States team at 2012 London Olympics, announces her retirement.

headline.main: Kyla Ross, U.S. Gold Medalist, Retires

snippet: Ross, the youngest member of the United States team that won a gold medal at the 2012 London Olympics, announced her retirement from elite competition.
lead_paragraph: Ross, the youngest member of the United States team that won a gold medal at the 2012 London Olympics, announced her retirement from elite competition.
